// idi8b_logo.h - "I Dream in 8 Bits" brand logo, original TEXT-mode
// screen-dump byte layout, reused as DATA (not displayed via the real
// TEXT-mode hardware any more -- see src/section_splash.c's own header
// comment for why the whole section moved to HIRES mode).
//
// Byte-identical copy of idi8b_logo[520] from Xander Mol's own sibling
// project locifilemanager-v2 (src/splash_data.h) -- same author, same
// brand, reused verbatim, not an external/third-party asset. That file's
// own header comment: "40x13 Oric screen-RAM dump (rows 0-12 of the 40x28
// text screen). Rows 0-10 hold the graphic logo, row 12 the text
// 'IDreamtIn8Bits.com'... Supplied by Xander Mol as IDI8B.dat (raw screen
// capture), trimmed to drop the redundant blank trailing rows."
//
// A raw byte-for-byte TEXTVRAM-layout dump: values < 0x20 are Oric
// TEXT-mode attribute-setting codes (ink/paper/alt-charset select),
// values >= 0x20 are character codes -- 0x21/0x30/0x35 are the mosaic
// wordmark's own glyph codes (rows 0-11), the last row (12) is plain
// ASCII ("IDreamtIn8Bits.com"). section_splash.c walks rows 0-11 only,
// using the embedded ink-attribute bytes to place colour brackets and the
// embedded 0x21/0x30/0x35 codes to look up their own known glyph bitmaps
// (assets/idi8b_altcharset.h) -- row 12 (the plain-text row) is NOT drawn
// from this array at all; "IDreamtIn8Bits.com" is drawn separately via
// hb_put_chars_center() instead.

